                         THE LAGOM LICENSE
                    Version 1, February 2026

    "Not too much, not too little — just the right amount of freedom."

TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR USE, REPRODUCTION, AND DISTRIBUTION
OF THIS SOFTWARE, OR WHATEVER THIS IS, HONESTLY

PREAMBLE

Most licenses are either too restrictive or too permissive.
The MIT License wants you to keep a copyright notice around like
a receipt you'll never need. The GPL wants you to share everything
like it's kindergarten. The UNLICENSE pretends law doesn't exist.
The WTFPL tells you to do what the fuck you want, which, while
admirable in spirit, lacks a certain Scandinavian restraint.

This license is lagom — just the right amount.

DEFINITIONS

"The Software" refers to whatever you found this license
attached to. Code, text, interpretive dance notation — we
don't judge.

"You" refers to the person reading this. Yes, you. The one
wondering if this is legally binding. (It's not. Or is it?
Lagom ambiguity.)

"Lagom" (Swedish, adj.) — not too much, not too little. The
Goldilocks zone, but with better furniture and meatballs.

"The Author" refers to whoever was producing this code instead
of going outside. Bless them.

GRANT OF RIGHTS

1. USAGE: You may use this software for any purpose, commercial
   or otherwise. Do not use it to power a galactic empire, but
   do not let it sit idle and gather dust either. The Author
   trusts you to be reasonable about it.

2. DISTRIBUTION: You may copy, merge, publish, distribute,
   sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software. If you share
   this code, don't make a big deal out of it. Don't hide it
   behind a paywall, but don't give it away with a parade either.
   Just put it there.

3. ATTRIBUTION: You should credit the author, but don't put
   their name in 40pt bold font. A small acknowledgment in the
   header is enough. Let's not get carried away. It's lagom.

4. MODIFICATIONS: You may modify the Software. If you change
   the code, make it better, but not too much better. We don't
   want the original author feeling inadequate.

5. LICENSE INCLUSION: Include this license or a reference to it
   in copies of the software. It's just polite.

6. You are NOT required to:
   a) Share your modifications
      (but hoarding is not lagom)
   b) Feel guilty about anything
      (guilt is never lagom)

7. You ARE encouraged to:
   a) Be a decent human being
   b) Take a walk sometimes
   c) Drink water
   d) Push to main on Fridays only if it feels lagom

LIMITATIONS OF LIABILITY

If the code breaks, that is unfortunate, but expected. Don't
sue the author; they did a reasonable job. If it works perfectly,
don't over-praise them either. It's just code.

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WHICH IS A LEGAL WAY OF
SAYING "GOOD LUCK". THE AUTHOR MAKES NO WARRANTIES, EXPRESS
OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF
MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR THAT
THE CODE ACTUALLY WORKS.

IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES,
OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT, OR
OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE
SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.

SERIOUSLY. IF THIS CODE DELETES YOUR DATABASE, BURNS YOUR
TOAST, OR CAUSES AN INTERNATIONAL INCIDENT, THAT IS BETWEEN
YOU AND YOUR BACKUP STRATEGY.

THE LAGOM CLAUSE

If at any point you feel that your use of this software has
become excessive, obsessive, or otherwise un-lagom, you are
encouraged to step away, have a fika, and return when balance
has been restored.

Similarly, if you feel you are under-using this software, you
are encouraged to use it a little more. Not too much. Just
lagom.

DISPUTE RESOLUTION

Any disputes arising from this license shall be resolved by
the involved parties sitting down over coffee and a cinnamon
bun, discussing the matter calmly until a lagom resolution is
reached. If no resolution is reached, both parties shall shrug
and move on with their lives.

Litigation is never lagom.

TERMINATION

This license is perpetual and irrevocable. It cannot be
terminated, because termination is too dramatic. It simply
exists, quietly, in the background, like a well-designed
piece of Swedish furniture.

FINAL WORDS

This software is free. Free as in speech, free as in beer,
free as in that IKEA pencil you definitely did not steal but
somehow ended up in your pocket.

Do what is sensible. Don't be a hero, and don't be a nuisance.
Keep it lagom.
